Actuary Needed

   This challenging, non-supervisory position allows you to do unique,
   cutting-edge work. It offers the right candidate a competitive salary
   plus a possible one-time bonus, good benefits, and relocation
   assistance. The application deadline is February 20, 2002.

Senior Actuary, Risk Management Agency, U.S. Department of Agriculture

   USDA's Risk Management Agency (RMA) is responsible for managing the
   programs of the Federal Crop Insurance Corporation (FCIC). The mission
   of RMA and FCIC is to improve the economic stability of American
   agriculture by providing producers access to effective crop insurances
   and other risk-management tools.

   The Senior Actuary reports to the Deputy Administrator for Research and
   Development in Kansas City, Missouri. This Office implements the
   various crop insurance and risk management programs supported by RMA,
   including policies, forms, rates, and regulations, as well managing
   actuarial and underwriting issues in general. Key responsibilities
   include:
     * Providing primary leadership in formulating, analyzing, and
       establishing national rate-making policy;
     * Advising the FCIC Board of Directors and RMA and USDA leadership on
       rates as well as on private insurance products submitted for
       reinsurance;
     * Defining corporate business requirements for various program,
       rating, and underwriting activities;
     * Advising RMA and USDA on program budget policy and strategy; and
     * Estimating costs for national program changes in proposed
       legislation.

   The salary range is approximately $122,000 to $138,000. Ideal
   candidates would have good quantitative skills and actuarial
   experience. Economic (agricultural, resource, or general) skills and
   experience are a definite plus.

   For details, see our on-line listing. (PDF file)

   To apply, you may use the OF-612: Optional Application for Federal
   Employment.

   For additional information concerning this position, please contact
   Nelson Maurice, nelson.maurice@rm.fcic.usda.gov or 816-926-7914.

                        An Equal Opportunity Employer

